reviews.text: Unexpected hospitality.  Services provided by the team of young and energetic floor staff was way above average here in Hong Kong.  They are also like super attentive.  This is the one thing that can’t be trained.  It takes initiative in the young people to work hard.  Coupled with tasty ramen from Japan, it was a very enjoyable lunching experience, albeit a really quick one.  This shop is so high on my list that I have no reservation recommending it.

The ramen chain Ippudo recently opened another restaurant in a retail space inside the Eaton Hotel. There were plenty of empty tables on a weekend evening, so there wasn’t a wait whatsoever. I had the cucumber dish (the name of which I forgot) which I liked and would recommend, as well as their well-known Tonkotsu ramen. The broth was rich and was delicious, and the noodles had a good texture. The meat was also nicely cut, with no fat being left behind. Ippudo served a good bowl of ramen that I enjoyed, and I would recommend it to anybody looking for a good Tonkotsu ramen.
Newly setup ramen shop, good food and excellent service

reviews.text: Room was good, clean, comfortable but a bit small. Got a great value deal tho for our stay that included the club lounge experience. Excellent attentiveness by the staff who made you feel like valued guests. Breakfast had a great array of choice and was quality.  Eaton is conveniently located and within walking distance of many tourist attractions and other hidden gems in Hong Kong. Eaton is a busy,  vibrant place for a Honkers holiday.

Nice modern hotel. I appreciate what they are trying to do with the more progressive and environmental messaging throughout the building. Rooms are on the small side but decently apportioned. Service is friendly. There is certainly lots to eat here too!

Nice and clean room and very helpful staff. Location also is superb. Steps away from train. Price is reasonable.
Rooms are a bit small.

It was very good in every area really.  Well situated on Nathan  rd., plenty of shops around, lots of life. Felt very safe. only a 15 min walk to Jordan station, only one stop away from harbour area. Staff polite and spoke good english.

Really well designed and a fantastic change from the old hotel.
Workshop was really cool and the food court excellent. Such a shame it's at that end of Nathan Road, but maybe it will kickstart a rejuvenation of Jordan!
Don't miss it if you happen to find yourself on the dark side!
